metadata.name: Pink Hyacinths
metadata.description:
Miss Saigon Hyacinths were my favourite flowers growing up, tiptoeing around my grandparent's greenhouse which to me felt like a it reached the skies with flowers, which in reality was only a tiny shed.

Hyacinths were the only flowers I could reach, but intrigued by my grandparents I wanted nothing more than to be able to help take care of the flowers myself. Sometimes I would try to hide a plantpot under my shirt to take back to my room and take care of them and each time I would be made to walk them back to the greenhouse after being caught by my grams.

Ever since those sneeky days I'd always wanted to own my own greenhouse filled with Hyacinths.

--

This series of greenhouses has a special place in my heart, inspired my love for botany and gardening ingrained into my by my grandfather,
